 <preface xml:id="preface">
  <title>Preface</title>
  <para>
   This manual describes how to install, use and extend NixOS, a Linux
   distribution based on the purely functional package management system Nix.
  </para>
  <para>
   If you encounter problems, please report them on the
   <literal
    xlink:href="https://discourse.nixos.org">Discourse</literal>
   or on the <link
    xlink:href="irc://irc.freenode.net/#nixos">
   <literal>#nixos</literal> channel on Freenode</link>. Bugs should be
   reported in
   <link
    xlink:href="https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/issues">NixOSâ€™
   GitHub issue tracker</link>.
  </para>
  <note>
   <para>
    Commands prefixed with <literal>#</literal> have to be run as root, either
    requiring to login as root user or temporarily switching to it using
    <literal>sudo</literal> for example.
   </para>
  </note>
 </preface>
